The paper proposes a new learning algorithm for building fuzzy rule-based classification systems for Big Data. The algorithm involves preprocessing, rule induction, and rule selection stages. The paper focuses on the accuracy and interpretability of the models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also deals with Big Data classification problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
